    <svcsection svcsectype="prodspec" date="02/26/1997" division="ENGINE" id="e12503">
        <title>SECTION 1: ENGINE CONTROL SYSTEM OVERVIEW - SECTION 1.3: INJECTOR OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INJECTOR OPERATION</title>
            <para>When an injector is energized, (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1250301">1.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) the poppet valve is opened by an electronic solenoid mounted on the injector. Oil pressure is allowed
                to flow into the injector and act on the amplifier piston. When injection is ended the pressure on top
                of the amplifier piston is vented by the poppet valve thru the top portion of the injector and directed
                by the oil troughs mounted on the injector to a push tube hole for return to the oil sump.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1250301" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1095" filename="../figeg1/eg1095.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.11 - Energized vs. De-energized Injector</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsection>
